name: Glass Terrarium
notes: Excellent visibility. Good humidity retention.

name: PVC Enclosure
notes: Superior humidity retention. Professional quality.

name: Screen Enclosure
notes: Maximum airflow. Excellent for low-humidity species.

name: UVB Linear Fixture
notes: Essential for vitamin D3 synthesis.

name: Ceramic Heat Emitter (CHE)
notes: Use thermostat to prevent overheating. NO heat mats (burn risk).

name: Bioactive Substrate Mix
notes: DIYing is easy and cost-effective!

name: Soil-Based Substrate
notes: Good for plants and naturalistic setups.

name: Paper-Based Substrate
notes: Easy to replace and clean.

name: Foam Substrate
notes: Lightweight and reusable.

name: Drainage Layer (LECA or clay balls)
notes: Essential for bioactive setups.

name: Drainage Barrier (mesh screen)
notes: Prevents substrate from mixing with drainage layer.

name: Springtail Culture
notes: Critical part of cleanup crew for bioactive environments.

name: Isopod Culture (Dwarf White)
notes: Reproduce quickly and are easy to manage.

name: Climbing Branches & Perches
notes: Cork bark and manzanita recommended.

name: Plants (live or artificial)
notes: Artificial easier for beginners. Live plants for naturalistic setups.

name: Live Plants
notes: Pothos and ferns are reliable starters.

name: Artificial Plants
notes: Easy to maintain and won't wilt.

name: Automated Misting System
notes: Great for consistent humidity without manual misting.

name: Ultrasonic or Cool Mist Humidifier
notes: Keep clean and use food-safe (no essential oils).

name: Fogger (Ultrasonic Humidification)
notes: Great for bioactive setups with plants.

name: Digital Thermometer & Hygrometer
notes: Monitor both warm and cool zones.
